gobblin.runtime.mapreduce

Class GobblinOutputCommitter

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.hadoop.mapreduce.OutputCommitter
      • gobblin.runtime.mapreduce.GobblinOutputCommitter

  • public class GobblinOutputCommitter
extends OutputCommitter
    Hadoop OutputCommitter implementation that overrides the default abortJob(JobContext, org.apache.hadoop.mapreduce.JobStatus.State) behavior. This is necessary to add functionality for cleaning up staging data when the JobLauncher.cancelJob(gobblin.runtime.JobListener) method is called via Azkaban. Azkaban only allows the cancel method run to for 5 ms until it does a hard kill on the process. In order to make sure the staging data still gets cleaned-up, the cleanup will take place in the AM.
